We need to figure out what to do about the Quot/Rem operator trait naming, ideally before `stage0` is updated again. My suggestion:

``` rust
pub trait Div<RHS,Result> {
    fn div(&self, rhs: &RHS) -> Result;
}

pub trait Rem<RHS,Result> {
    fn rem(&self, rhs: &RHS) -> Result;
}

pub trait Integer: Num
                 + Orderable
                 + Div<Self,Self>
                 + Rem<Self,Self> {
    fn div_rem(&self, other: &Self) -> (Self,Self);

    fn div_floor(&self, other: &Self) -> Self;
    fn mod_floor(&self, other: &Self) -> Self;
    fn div_mod_floor(&self, other: &Self) -> (Self,Self);

    fn div_euclid(&self, other: &Self) -> Self;
    fn mod_euclid(&self, other: &Self) -> Self;
    fn div_mod_euclid(&self, other: &Self) -> (Self,Self);

    //...
}
```

See [Division and Modulus for Computer Scientists](http://research.microsoft.com/pubs/151917/divmodnote-letter.pdf) for a good explanation of the differences between the operations.

